commit.message:
e2tools has moved: Remove all files except for README.md

e2tools has moved. This removes all files except for README.md
which has been changed to explain where and how the move has gone.
README.md: Reformat headings
Reformat old README as markdown in README.md
Use COPYING file with updated FSF address
call it e2tools-0.0.16.4

configure.ac: give hint where to find libext2fs

libext2fs is shipped as part of e2fsprogs.
gitignore: clean up

enlarge buffer so that everything will fit

Discovered by gcc -Wformat-security.
silence compiler warnings on unused vars and undefined functions
Remove redundant comment line
Renamed configure.in -> configure.ac
Add man pages (courtesy of Lucas Wall at Debian)
Require libext2fs >= 1.27
Add gnulib-added .m4, .c, and .h files to repo
How to build from git repo
Use pkg-config for the libs, avoid AM_PROG_CC_C_O
Remove Makefile.in files from repository

Avoid signed/unsigned comparison, and = in expr

This concludes the warning extermination exercise. Now the beast
builds with CPPFLAGS="-Wall -Wextra -Werrror"!
Remove config.h.in from repository

Define all u?int(8|16|32|64)_t types

Just in case we are going to use it somewhere.
Include errno.h as we're using errno
Explicitly cast ext2_off_t to (signed) int32_t
Explicitly cast unsigned expressions to int
Add gnulib's stdint.h and inttypes.h
Remove autoreconf generated files from git

Modernizing configure.ac

Preparing for gnulib's inttypes.h and stdint.h
Use one foo.h file per foo.c
Make it work with automake-1.10
Get rid of 64bit formatstring warning
